<P>In the chancel of the parish church of St. Mary, Whitechapel, are the following monuments: 
<P>&ldquo;<hi rend=italics>M.S.</hi> To the memory of Judith Meggs, widow, the beloved wife of William Meggs, of this parish, Esq. &amp;c. <datestruct value="1662--"><year reg="1662">1662</year></datestruct>, aged <num value="83">83</num>. And the said William her husband, <datestruct value="1620--"><year reg="1620">1620</year></datestruct>. 
<P>&ldquo;William Meggs, Esq. and James Meggs, D.D. their <num value="2">two</num> sons, caused this monument to be erected. 
<P>&ldquo;William Meggs, Esq. <datestruct value="1678--"><year reg="1678">1678</year></datestruct>, who was a most worthy member of this parish, and the principal benefactor towards the re-edifying of this house of God. His loving nephew, Sir William Goulston, Knt in much gratitude erected this monument.&rdquo; 
